There's one! He's out! Go get him, yellow shirts!

5
00:00:31,195 --> 00:00:31,716
No, just kidding.

6
00:00:31,736 --> 00:00:33,177
But please, if you can turn that on and off.

7
00:00:33,237 --> 00:00:35,339
And also, no laser pointers, please.

8
00:00:35,359 --> 00:00:36,380
That's disruptive.

9
00:00:36,420 --> 00:00:36,781
Thank you.

10
00:00:38,602 --> 00:00:41,825
This is really an historic moment for the Game Developers

11
00:00:41,865 --> 00:00:43,747
Conference and for the community that it serves.

12
00:00:45,008 --> 00:00:48,031
Four years ago, when Miller Freeman began working with

13
00:00:48,051 --> 00:00:50,914
this event, we asked our conference advisory board,

14
00:00:51,774 --> 00:00:53,816
what would the dream conference look like?

15
00:00:54,717 --> 00:00:57,460
What would be the pinnacle of success for this event?

16
00:00:59,168 --> 00:01:02,510
The answer, as voiced by one Ernest Adams, came in two

17
00:01:02,570 --> 00:01:05,571
simple words, Shigeru Miyamoto.

18
00:01:15,736 --> 00:01:17,157
Well, much has happened since then.

19
00:01:17,357 --> 00:01:20,379
We've had four wonderful years, literally hundreds of

20
00:01:20,459 --> 00:01:25,041
inspiring speakers, many great parties, and wonderful

21
00:01:25,081 --> 00:01:25,981
connections have been made.

22
00:01:27,329 --> 00:01:30,291
But this year, our dream of four years has come to fruition.

23
00:01:31,472 --> 00:01:34,274
There is no greater validation of this community and this

24
00:01:34,354 --> 00:01:37,776
event than the presence of the world master of game design.

25
00:01:38,977 --> 00:01:42,119
I'm going to ask you all to help me answer the question

26
